{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"9":{"eng-name":"Zakat (Kitab Al-Zakat)","ara-name":"كتاب الزكاة"}},"section_detail":{"9":{"hadithnumber_first":1556,"hadithnumber_last":1700,"arabicnumber_first":1556,"arabicnumber_last":1700}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1598,"arabicnumber":1598,"text":"Waki’ said Ba’l means the agricultural crop which grows by the rain water. Ibn Al Aswad said and Yahya, that is, Ibn Adam said I asked Abu Iyas al Asadi (about this word ba’l). He replied What is watered by rain","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih Maqtu"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih Maqtu"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Isnaad Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":9,"hadith":43},"chapter":{"id":12,"ara-name":"باب صَدَقَةِ الزَّرْعِ","eng-name":"Zakat On Agricultural Produce","isFirstHadith":false}}]}